//Fracture – Tibia proximal AO 41 - 41B: Partial articular



Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select 'Fracture – Tibia proximal AO 41' from the Finding dropdown
And I select '41B: Partial articular' radio button

Then '41B1: Split fracture' radio button is enabled
And '41B2: Impression' radio button is enabled
And '41B3: Split-depression fracture' radio button is enabled


When I select '41B1: Split fracture' radio button
Then '41B1.1: Lateral tibial plateau' radio button is enabled
And '41B1.1: Medial tibial plateau' radio button is enabled
And '41B1.3: Oblique fracture involving the diaphysis' radio button is enabled

When I select '41B1.3: Oblique fracture involving the diaphysis' radio button
then 'f: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And 'h: Medial' radio button is enabled
And 'Depression depth in mm' input field is enabled


When I select '41B2: Impression' radio button
Then '41B2.1: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And '41B2.2: Medial' radio button is enabled

When I select '41B2.1: Lateral' radio button
then 't: Anterolateral (AL)' radio button is enabled
And 'u: Posteriolateral (PL)' radio button is enabled
And 'x: Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Depression depth in mm' input field is enabled

When I select '41B2.2: Medial' radio button
then 'v: Anteromedial (AM)' radio button is enabled
And 'w: Posteriomedial (PM)' radio button is enabled
And 'x: Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Depression depth in mm' input field is enabled


When I select '41B3: Split-depression fracture' radio button
Then '41B3.1: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And '41B3.2: Medial' radio button is enabled
And '41B3.3: Oblique fracture involving the diaphysis' radio button is enabled

When I select '41B3.1: Lateral' radio button
then 't: Anterolateral (AL)' radio button is enabled
And 'u: Posteriolateral (PL)' radio button is enabled
And 'x: Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Depression depth in mm' input field is enabled

When I select '41B3.2: Medial' radio button
then 'v: Anteromedial (AM)' radio button is enabled
And 'w: Posteriomedial (PM)' radio button is enabled
And 'x: Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Depression depth in mm' input field is enabled

When I select '41B3.3: Oblique fracture involving the diaphysis' radio button
then 'f: Lateral' radio button is enabled
And 'h: Medial' radio button is enabled
And 'Depression depth in mm' input field is enabled 
